{{refimprove|date=January 2016}} {{Infobox company |name=TLA Releasing |location=[[United States]] |products=[[Motion pictures]], [[DVD]]s |type=[[Film distribution]] }}
'''TLA Releasing''' is a US film distribution company owned by [[TLA Entertainment Group]]. In March 2011, a new LLC was formed for the operation.<ref>{{cite web|title=TLA Releasing Sold to Group Spearheaded by Derek Curl|url=http://www.indiewire.com/article/tla_releasing_sold_to_group_spearheaded_by_derek_curl |work=indieWIRE.com |accessdate=September 3, 2011|author=Brian Brooks |date=May 3, 2011}}</ref> Its primary output is [[LGBT]]-related films from all over the world under the "TLA Releasing" label, as well as [[horror film]]s under the label "Danger After Dark". Since 2000, they have released over 200 films on DVD and various VOD platforms.
In 2005, they opened a branch in the UK. In June 2011, they announced "TLA Select", a line of [[Blu-ray]]s of TLA Releasing's most popular films, including ''[[Latter Days]]'', ''[[Another Gay Movie]]'' and ''[[Another Gay Sequel]]'', ''[[Make the Yuletide Gay]]'', and ''[[Boy Culture]]''.<ref>{{cite web|title=TLA Releasing Makes a Move to Blu-Rays|url=http://www.indiewire.com/article/tla_releasing_makes_a_move_to_blu-rays/|work=indieWIRE.com |author=Nigel M Smith |date=June 29, 2011 }}</ref>
In July 2011, the UK division lost its entire inventory of DVDs when rioters in London burnt down a Sony warehouse.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://news.pinkpaper.com/NewsStory/5860/10/08/2011/exclusive-second-gay-film-company-lose-stock-in-warehouse-riot-blaze.aspx |title=Exclusive: Second gay film company lose stock in warehouse riot blaze |work=PinkPaper.com |author=Peter Lloyd |date=August 10, 2011 |accessdate=September 3, 2011 |archiveurl=https://archive.today/20120718073041/http://news.pinkpaper.com/NewsStory/5860/10/08/2011/exclusive-second-gay-film-company-lose-stock-in-warehouse-riot-blaze.aspx |archivedate=18 July 2012 |deadurl=yes |df= }}</ref> Sony rapidly worked to replenish the lost stock.
