{{More citations needed|date=October 2018}} [[File:Palacio de Golestán, Teherán, Irán, 2016-09-17, DD 27-36 HDR PAN.jpg|thumb|300px|Āina-kāri in the main hall of ''Emarat-e Badgir'' in [[Golestan Palace]]]] '''Āina-kāri'''<ref>http://www.iranicaonline.org/articles/aina-kari-mosaic-of-mirror-glass</ref> ({{lang-fa|آینه‌کاری}}) is a kind of [[interior decoration]] by putting small pieces of mirror together in [[geometric]] forms or in forms of flowers and shrubs. By this art, a craftsman creates a beautiful shining space in a building with cut mirrors in various forms. The reflex of light through numberless formed mirror pieces gives out brightness and effulgence. Beside the decoration use, this art is used as a strong durable cover for an interior space of a building.<ref>{{cite book|first= |last=Moein|title=Farhang-e Moein|trans-title=Moein Persian Dictionary|publisher=|isbn=|editor-first=|editor-last=|page=|language=Persian|year=2004}}</ref>
